aria-allowed-attr-1.title: `[aria-*]` attributes do not match their roles
aria-allowed-attr-1.description: Each ARIA `role` supports a specific subset of `aria-*` attributes. Mismatching these invalidates the `aria-*` attributes. [Learn how to match ARIA attributes to their roles](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/aria-allowed-attr).

frame-title-3.title: `<frame>` or `<iframe>` elements do not have a title
frame-title-3.description: Screen reader users rely on frame titles to describe the contents of frames. [Learn more about frame titles](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/frame-title).

link-in-text-block-4.title: Links rely on color to be distinguishable.
link-in-text-block-4.description: Low-contrast text is difficult or impossible for many users to read. Link text that is discernible improves the experience for users with low vision. [Learn how to make links distinguishable](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/link-in-text-block).

target-size-6.title: Touch targets do not have sufficient size or spacing.
target-size-6.description: Touch targets with sufficient size and spacing help users who may have difficulty targeting small controls to activate the targets. [Learn more about touch targets](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.10/target-size).
